<!DOCTYPE html>
<%# Type: static
		Catorgory: info %>
<html lang="en-US">

<head>
	<title>clutters -- API docs</title>
	<%- include("headTag") -%>
</head>

<body>
	<%- include("header") -%>
	<div id="content">
		<h1>API</h1>
		These are the docs for the API(the backend isn't set up, so it only return debug data right now). All of them are under the endpoint <span class="code">/<span class="inner">api</span>/</span>, and return <a href="https://www.json.org/json-en.html">JSON</a> files.
		<h2 id="clutters">Clutter Info</h2>
		Get data on clutterss<br>
		Please note that as of currently, It only returns info about the debug clutters.
		<div class="code">/<span class="inner">api</span>/<span class="inner">clutters</span>/<span class="quote">:</span><span class="number">id</span></div>
		Example response:
		<div class="code">
			{
			<div style="margin-left:1em">
  			<span class="quote">"name"</span>: <span class="inner">"name:)"</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"creator"</span>: <span class="inner">"Steve0Greatness"</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"included"</span>: [<span class="quote">"588586405"</span>, <span class="quote">"487519987"</span>],<br>
  			<span class="quote">"date"</span>: <span class="inner">"Sat, Nov 13 2021"</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"thumb"</span>: <span class="number">0</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"id"</span>: <span class="number">1</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"remix"</span>: [<span class="inner">true</span>, <span class="inner">"2"</span>, <span class="inner">"S0G"</span>, <span class="inner">"Yes?"</span>]</div>
			}
		</div>
		<h3 id="clutters-Comments">Comments</h3>
		Doesn't work yet, comments don't exist.
		<div class="code">/<span class="inner">api</span>/<span class="inner">clutters</span>/<span class="quote">:</span><span class="number">id</span>/<span class="inner">comments</span></div>
		Example response:
		<div class="code">
			{
			<div style="margin-left:1em">
				<span class="quote">"notice"</span>: <span class="inner">"Comments can't currently be read"</span>,<br>
				<span class="quote">"error"</span>: <span class="inner">"NotYours"</span>
  		</div>
			}
		</div>
		<h3 id="clutters-Thumbnail">Thumbnail</h3>
		<div class="code">/<span class="inner">api</span>/<span class="inner">clutters</span>/<span class="quote">:</span><span class="number">id</span>/<span class="inner">thumbnail.png</span></div>
		Redirects the thumbnail of the project defined as the thumbnail for the Clutter.
		<h2 id="User">User Info</h2>
		Users don't have info yet
		<div class="code">/<span class="inner">api</span>/<span class="inner">users</span>/<span class="quote">:</span><span class="number">name</span></div>
		Example response:
		<div class="code">
			{<div style="margin-left:1em">
  			<span class="quote">"name"</span>: <span class="inner">"Steve0Greatness"</span>,<br>
				<span class="quote">"id"</span>: <span class="number">61820378</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"clutters"</span>: [<div style="margin-left:1em">
					<span class="quote">"name"</span>: <span class="inner">"name:)"</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"creator"</span>: <span class="inner">"Steve0Greatness"</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"included"</span>: [<span class="quote">"588586405"</span>, <span class="quote">"487519987"</span>],<br>
  			<span class="quote">"date"</span>: <span class="inner">"Sat, Nov 13 2021"</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"thumb"</span>: <span class="number">0</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"id"</span>: <span class="number">1</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"remix"</span>: [<span class="inner">true</span>, <span class="quote">"2"</span>, <span class="quote">"S0G"</span>, <span class="quote">"Yes?"</span>]</div>
				]</div>
			}</div>
			<h3 id="User-avartar">Avartar</h3>
			<div class="code">/<span class="inner">api</span>/<span class="inner">users</span>/<span class="quote">:</span><span class="number">name</span>/<span class="inner">avartar.png</span></div>
			<p>Redirects to the profile picture of the user on Scratch. I'd say it's possibly the easiest way to get a user's profile picture.</p>
			<h2 id="Featured">Featured clutterss</h2>
		<div class="code">/<span class="inner">api</span>/<span class="inner">featured</span></div>
		Example response:
		<div class="code">
			[{
			<div style="margin-left:1em">
  			<span class="quote">"name"</span>: <span class="inner">"name:)"</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"creator"</span>: <span class="inner">"Steve0Greatness"</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"included"</span>: [<span class="quote">"588586405"</span>, <span class="quote">"487519987"</span>],<br>
  			<span class="quote">"date"</span>: <span class="inner">"Sat, Nov 13 2021"</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"thumb"</span>: <span class="number">0</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"id"</span>: <span class="number">1</span>,<br>
  			<span class="quote">"remix"</span>: [<span class="inner">true</span>, <span class="quote">"2"</span>, <span class="quote">"S0G"</span>, <span class="quote">"Yes?"</span>]</div>
			},<br>
			...]
		</div>
	</div>
		</div>
	<%- include("footer") -%>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="/script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>